extends layout.pug

block content
    secton(class='section')
        div(class='columns is-centered')
            div(class='column is-11') 
                article(class='message')
                    div(class='message-header')
                        p Welcome
                    div(class='message-body')
                        p(class='is-size-6')
                            |This site was built as a learning project to learn web development.
                            |I had a need to test and use some Microsoft Azure B2C APIs.
                            |Once I figured out how the API worked, I started thiking of ways the API could be
                            |built into a web app, and so my adventure began.
                        br
                        p(class='is-size-6')
                            |Through the process of building this site I have learned how to use and implement
                            |the techologies below. The are all currently in use in dvelopment of this site.
                        br
        div(class='container is-fluid')
            div(class='columns is-centered')
                 div(class='column is-11')
                    div(class='columns')
                        div(class='column')
                            article(class='media notification is-link')
                                figure(class='media-left')
                                    p(class='image is-64x64')
                                        img(src='images/node.png')
                                div(class='media-content')
                                    div(class='content')
                                        h1(class='title is-size-5')
                                            a(href='https://nodejs.org/en/') Node JS
                                        p(class='is-size-7') As an asynchronous event-driven JavaScript runtime, Node.js is designed to build scalable network applications. Many connections can be handled concurrently.
                        div(class='column') 
                            article(class='media notification is-link')
                                figure(class='media-left')
                                    p(class='image is-64x64')
                                        img(src='images/pug.svg')
                                div(class='media-content')
                                    div(class='content')
                                        h1(class='title is-size-5')
                                            a(href='https://pugjs.org') Pug
                                        p(class='is-size-7') Pug is a high-performance template engine heavily influenced by Haml and implemented with JavaScript for Node.js and browsers.

                        div(class='column') 
                            article(class='media notification is-link')
                                figure(class='media-left')
                                    p(class='image is-64x64' href='https://bulma.io/')
                                        img(src='images/bulma.png')
                                div(class='media-content')
                                    div(class='content')
                                        h1(class='title is-size-5')
                                            a(href='https://bulma.io/') Bulma
                                        p(class='is-size-7') Bulma is a free, open source CSS framework based on Flexbox and used by more than 200,000 developers.